&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;SS-0100 Corporate Services Officer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen in the Devon Doctors Ltd Corporate Services Team for a Corporate Services Officer based at our Exeter HQ, Osprey House. This is a full time position, 40 hours per week, providing support to management. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This role attracts an annual salary of between £22,000 and £23,500 dependant on experience. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As Corporate Services Assistant you will support the Corporate Services Lead, by providing general administrative assistance to the maintenance and compliance of the organisation’s policies and procedures. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To deal with information requests in accordance with legislation and assist the organisation to meet data protection requirements. In addition, you will support the training and development of employees in relation to information governance and data protection and you will be the first point of contact for any staff compliance queries. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ideal candidate for this role will have experience of data protection, information governance and records management and a positive attitude towards developing knowledge and skills in these areas. This position could suit somebody with a law degree or equivalent as this role requires up-to-date knowledge of data protection and information governance legislation however full training will be provided to the right candidate. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Further details of the role are provided in the Job Description.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Devon Doctors has been delivering urgent primary care in Devon to an exceptional standard for over twenty years.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Currently with the Integrated Urgent Care Service (IUCS) for Devon, Integrated Urgent Care Service (IUCS) Somerset. Our sister companies include Access Health and Access Dental who offer a range of dentistry and primary care services across the Peninsula.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Benefits of working for us include:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;22 days holiday (plus Bank Holidays)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Pension&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cycle to work scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 Paid Volunteering day per year&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discounts at retailers via Perkbox&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Free 24 hour Employee Assistance Programme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are committed to being an inclusive employer with a diverse workforce. We encourage applications from people from all backgrounds, cultures and experiences to contribute to the diversity of our organisation. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
